The semi-perimeter of the triangle is $(11 + 13 + 20)/2 = 22$, so by Heron's formula, the area of triangle $ABC$ is $$\sqrt{22(22 - 11)(22 - 13)(22 - 20)} = 66.$$Hence, the height of triangle $ABC$ with respect to base $BC$ is $AQ = 2 \cdot 66/BC = 2 \cdot 66/20 = 33/5$.  Therefore, $GP = AQ/3 = (33/5)/3 = \boxed{\frac{11}{5}}$. The answer is \frac{11}{5}

Setting $x = 4,$ we get
\[3f(4) - 2 f \left( \frac{1}{4} \right) = 4.\]Setting $x = \frac{1}{4},$ we get
\[3 f \left( \frac{1}{4} \right) - 2f(4) = \frac{1}{4}.\]We can view these equations as a system in $f(4)$ and $f \left( \frac{1}{4} \right).$  Solving this system, we find $f(4) = \boxed{\frac{5}{2}}.$. The answer is \frac{5}{2}

